      <div class="card-top">
        <div class="avatar" style="background:#ebe8ff; color:#5533bb;">FI</div>
        <div>
          <div class="card-title">Fi Money</div>
          <div class="card-sub">Neo-banking app for millennials & Gen Z — savings, spends, analytics</div>
          <div class="badges">
            <span class="badge b-fintech">Fintech</span>
            <span class="badge b-b2c">B2C</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="priority-row">
        <span class="priority-label">Priority</span>
        <div class="priority-bar"><div class="priority-fill" style="width:88%; background:#7f77dd;"></div></div>
        <span style="font-size:12px; color:#555; font-weight:600;">High</span>
      </div>
      <div class="info-grid">
        <div class="info-item"><label>Contact Person</label><p>Sumit Gwalani — Co-founder</p></div>
        <div class="info-item"><label>Website</label><a href="https://fi.money" target="_blank">fi.money ↗</a></div>
        <div class="info-item"><label>LinkedIn</label><a href="https://linkedin.com/company/fi-money" target="_blank">linkedin.com/company/fi-money ↗</a></div>
        <div class="info-item"><label>Best Contact Route</label><p>Growth / partnerships team on LinkedIn</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="collab-box">
        <div class="collab-title">Collaboration Opportunity</div>
        <p>Fi Money users track spending inside a closed ecosystem. Xpensease's SMS-based tracker works across all banks — making it perfect for Fi users splitting expenses with non-Fi friends. A cross-promotion or referral program targeting college students and young professionals in Tier-2 cities could expand both apps' installs simultaneously.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tags">
        <span class="tag">Cross-promotion</span><span class="tag">Referral Program</span><span class="tag">Gen Z Segment</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 3. Slice -->
